Claudetteia Love, 17, said last week that she and her friends would not attend Carroll High School's prom in Monroe, Louisiana, because Principal Patrick Taylor had told her she had to wear a tuxedo .
But now, Principal Taylor and Monroe City Board President Rodney McFarland have reportedly told her that she may wear the attire after all .
The National Center for Lesbian Rights said in a statement that the pair contacted the school to inform them of their decision .